hazard_Name: Tsunami Information (Hawaiian Islands) - In The Summit Region Of Kilauea Volcano - 5.4
description:
A Tsunami Information has been issued by NWS PACIFIC TSUNAMI WARNING CENTER EWA BEACH HI for IN THE SUMMIT REGION OF KILAUEA VOLCANO at July 20, 02:36:00 GMT.

Message:

000
WEHW42 PHEB 200236
TIBHWX
HIZ001>003-005>009-012>014-016>021-023>026-200436-
 
TSUNAMI INFORMATION STATEMENT NUMBER   1
NWS PACIFIC TSUNAMI WARNING CENTER EWA BEACH HI
436 PM HST THU JUL 19 2018
 
TO - EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT IN THE STATE OF HAWAII
 
SUBJECT - LOCAL TSUNAMI INFORMATION STATEMENT
 
THIS STATEMENT IS FOR INFORMATION ONLY. NO ACTION REQUIRED.
 
AN SEISMIC EVENT HAS OCCURRED NEAR THE SUMMIT OF KILAUEA VOLCANO.
THE EVENT IS LIKELY ASSOCIATED WITH A SUMMIT ERUPTION.
 
ITS PRELIMINARY PARAMETERS ARE
 
   ORIGIN TIME - 0433 PM HST 19 JUL 2018
   COORDINATES - 19.4 NORTH  155.3 WEST
   LOCATION    - IN THE SUMMIT REGION OF KILAUEA VOLCANO
   MAGNITUDE   - 5.4
 
EVALUATION
 
 NO TSUNAMI IS EXPECTED. REPEAT. NO TSUNAMI IS EXPECTED.
 
THIS WILL BE THE ONLY STATEMENT ISSUED FOR THIS EVENT UNLESS
ADDITIONAL DATA ARE RECEIVED.
 
$$


End of Message.
